headline: Intel (INTC): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, Intel has been a great trade, beating the S&P 500 by 14.9%. Its stock price has climbed to $23.42, representing a healthy 22% increase. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
